<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-194-181 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 611 317</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  March 27 1991 n155 p136(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Community care. (Qandamp;A) (letter to the editor)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Taylor, Daniel; Montgomery, Keith.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT/><TEXT>Community Care Companies and products are going missing.andP;  Searches have beenmade high and low -- the surgeons asked their friends and even their enemies,but nothing came to light.andP;  Perhaps you can helpandM;Q I use Matrix Layout for my programming, but now I have a bit of a problem.andO;I can't get in touch with Matrix Software Technology.andP;  This is especiallyworrying if I have a technical problem and also means that I won't be able toget or even hear about new upgrades.andM;From what I've heard, Matrix Software Technology has gone out of business inthe UK, but in the US it's still alive and kicking.andM;Please could you clear this small problem up, and if possible supply me withan address at which I can contact the company.andM;Q Do you have any information about what happened to the Perfect range ofsoftware -- PerfectCalc, Perfectwriter, Perfect filer and so on?andM;We're trying to trace the company -- if it exists -- which is currentlyproviding support.andP;  Do you know if CP/M software can be upgraded to MS-DOS?andM;A I'm afraid there's no way you can get your CP/M software to run on MS-DOS.andO;Your only hope is find out whether or not the software programs you use havebeen rewritten for MS-DOS.andO;</TEXT></DOC>